restrictions: This garage is for the exclusive use of Palmer House guests and patrons of its tenant businesses. Violators will be towed.
At high-volume times, the attendant may ask to valet your vehicle.
HERO TIP: Parking spaces at this facility are narrow, so smaller or compact vehicles are ideal for this location.
When you pull up the garage will say “Full,” however you will already have a reserved space so you will be fine to enter.
common.navigation_tip: Enter this location at 124 S Wabash Ave. This is the Palmer House garage operated by ABM Parking. It is located on the west/right-hand side of S Wabash Ave St (a one-way street) between E Monroe St and E Adams St. It is just past the Corner Bakery and just before the main entrance of the Palmer House. Please note: The address 124 S. Wabash is for GPS purposes, this address will not be displayed above the garage entrance, look for a black and gold sign stating "Parking" in white print.
common.title: 124 S Wabash Ave. - Garage

short_term.text: Complete the attached application. Once completed, please bring it to the garage office (located in the basement) when you start parking. Your spot will not be valid for the full month until this is completed.

Scan your QR code to enter the garage. Short term parker (1 month): You will use your QR code to enter the garage on your first visit. Afterwards, you will take a ticket at the entrance gate, and upon exit, you will use that same ticket and call out at the exit gate with your rental ID number.

Note: If you purchased your spot on or before 2/24/16 you are not eligible to receive a key fob. Please use your rental ID to go in/out.
Long term parker (2 months or more): You will be issued a key fob. Until you receive your key fob, read out your rental ID # at the exit gate.
Your card will be charged automatically each month until you cancel. If you would like to cancel this recurring charge, please email support@spothero.com
